        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 4 at 3:39PM MDT by NWS Missoula MT</headline>
        <description>At 337 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking an intense snow shower 14
miles north of West Glacier, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Visibility one-half mile or less.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Low visibility and heavy snow rates could result in
dangerous driving conditions. Winter driving conditions
near Logan Pass.
</description>
        <instruction>This storm may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional information
and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
